      <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8;">

        <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
          Many storage facilities in the Vernal area advertise "convenient access" but only allow entry during business hours — typically 7 AM to 7 PM, or even shorter on weekends and holidays. For oil field workers, contractors, hunters, and anyone who doesn't work a standard 9-to-5, restricted hours are a deal-breaker.
        </p>

        <h2 style="font-family: 'Georgia', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; color: var(--primary-dark); margin: 30px 0 15px;">True 24/7 — Every Hour, Every Day</h2>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Fort Knox Self Storage provides genuine 24-hour access, 365 days a year. When you rent a unit, you receive a personal access code for the gated entry. There are no blackout times, no holiday restrictions, no "closed for maintenance" windows. At 2 AM on Christmas morning, your code works exactly the same as it does at noon on a Tuesday.</p>

        <h2 style="font-family: 'Georgia', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; color: var(--primary-dark); margin: 30px 0 15px;">Who Needs 24-Hour Access in Vernal?</h2>

        <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 24px;">
          <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Oil field workers.</strong> Shift changes in the Basin happen around the clock. Grabbing tools or dropping off equipment at 4 AM is routine.</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Hunters.</strong> Opening morning means loading your trailer long before sunrise. Restricted access makes that impossible.</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Contractors.</strong> Early job site starts mean early material runs. Having 24/7 access to your supply container keeps projects on schedule.</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Families in transition.</strong> Moving doesn't always happen during business hours. Weekend and evening access without restrictions makes everything easier.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 style="font-family: 'Georgia', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; color: var(--primary-dark); margin: 30px 0 15px;">How Access Works</h2>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">When you sign your rental agreement, James gives you a personal access code for the gated entry to the Fort Knox yard. You use that code to enter any time, day or night. The driveways are wide enough for semis, so backing in a truck and trailer — even in the dark — is straightforward. And because each container has four padlock positions with your own locks, your unit stays secured between visits.</p>

        
